    excerpt: "Understanding the unique tire requirements of the Rolls-Royce Ghost — where ride quality, silence, and effortless comfort take absolute priority.",
    content: `## Rolls-Royce Ghost Tire Specifications

The Rolls-Royce Ghost is arguably the finest luxury sedan in the world. Its 6.75-liter twin-turbocharged V12 produces 563 horsepower, but the Ghost is not about speed — it is about absolute refinement. Rolls-Royce famously describes the driving experience as a "magic carpet ride," and the tires play a crucial role in delivering that sensation. Choosing the wrong tires for a Ghost is not just a performance issue; it fundamentally compromises the car's reason for existing.

### OEM Tire Sizes and Requirements

The current Rolls-Royce Ghost uses 255/45R21 tires on the front and 285/40R21 tires on the rear, mounted on 21-inch wheels. Some variants and optional wheel packages may use 255/40R22 front and 285/35R22 rear tires on 22-inch wheels. Rolls-Royce originally fits the Ghost with specially developed Pirelli P Zero tires that feature noise-canceling foam technology inside the tire cavity.

### The Importance of Acoustic Comfort

What makes Ghost tires unique is the emphasis on noise reduction. The foam liner inside the OEM Pirelli tires absorbs road noise before it can transfer through the wheel and into the cabin. When shopping for replacement tires, look for models with similar acoustic technology. Pirelli marks these with "PNCS" (Pirelli Noise Canceling System), Continental uses "ContiSilent," and Michelin offers "Acoustic" technology. These foam-lined tires make a genuinely noticeable difference in a car as quiet as the Ghost.

### Recommended Replacement Tires

The Pirelli P Zero PZ4 with PNCS technology is the direct replacement for the OEM tire and remains the top recommendation. The Continental SportContact 7 with ContiSilent is another excellent option that Ghost owners have praised for its refined ride quality and near-silent performance. For those seeking maximum comfort, the Michelin Pilot Sport EV (which includes acoustic foam) is worth considering, as its construction prioritizes ride smoothness.

### Load Rating Considerations

The Rolls-Royce Ghost weighs approximately 5,600 pounds, making proper load ratings essential. Never install tires with a lower load index than what Rolls-Royce specifies. The additional weight also means that tire pressures must be maintained diligently — even a few PSI of underinflation can dramatically affect ride quality, fuel economy, and tire longevity on a car this heavy.

### Tire Maintenance for the Ghost

Rolls-Royce recommends checking tire pressures every two weeks and before any long journey. The recommended pressures are typically 36 PSI front and 41 PSI rear for normal driving, though always verify with your specific model's door placard. Regular visual inspections for sidewall damage are also important, as the Ghost's low-profile tires on large-diameter wheels are vulnerable to pothole and curb damage.

### What to Budget

Tires for the Rolls-Royce Ghost are among the most expensive luxury sedan tires available, ranging from $400 to $700 per tire. A full set with mounting and balancing will typically cost between $2,000 and $3,500. At Ship.Tires, we carry foam-lined luxury fitments specifically suited to the Ghost's exacting standards. Your Rolls-Royce deserves nothing less than tires engineered to preserve its legendary ride quality.`,
